Sports Non-Verbal Communication Video Annotator  

# A lightweight web app for tagging, analyzing, and exporting non-verbal communication events in sports footage.

# Features/Controls:
- Upload new video intially or to replace current video
- play/pause button  
- Click to play/pause on the video  
- Progress bar  
- Volume control (mute + slider)  
- Playback speed controls (0.25× → 2×)  
- Keyboard Shortcuts:
  - Spacebar: Pause/Play
  - Left/Right Arrow: Jump forward/backward 3 seconds


---

# Annotation System
- Predefined non-verbal communication action buttons  
- Custom annotations (“Other”)  
- Automatic timestamping (video time + optional game clock)  
- Click an annotation to jump to that moment  
- Delete any annotation  
- Export all annotations as `annotations.json`  

Definitions:

- Eye Contact  
 - Intentional glance used to signal:
  - Readiness for a pass  
  - Acknowledgement of a defensive change  
  - Confirmation of a play or cut  

- Screen  
 - Indicates a screen is coming. Includes:
  - Moving toward a defender to set a pick  
  - Using a stance or gesture to signal where the screen will be  

- Directing (Gesturing / Pointing)  
 - Hand motions or body cues used to direct teammates:
  - Where to move  
  - When to cut  
  - Which play is being executed  

- Call for Ball  
  - Non-verbal gestures asking for a pass:
  - Open hand raised  
  - Hand extended toward passer  
  - Flashing open into space  

- Defensive Switch  
 - Silent defensive coordination:
  - Pointing at a new assignment  
  - Gesturing to swap matchups  
  - Eye contact + hand signal to change coverage  

- Nod  
 - A subtle confirmation cue:
  - “Run it now”  
  - “I’m ready”  
  - “I see the same read as you”  

- Other (Custom)  
 - User-defined events not covered above.  
  - Examples:
   - “Hand wave”  
   - “Tap on chest”  
   - “Backdoor signal”  


- Annotation Controls
 - Action Buttons: Add an annotation with that label 
  - Game Clock Input: Optional text like “10:45 Q2” 
  - Custom Annotation (“Other”): Enter custom label + click “Add Other” 
  - Annotation List: Shows events newest → oldest 
  - Click Annotation: Jump to annotation time 
  - Trash Icon: Delete annotation 
  - Export: Download "annotations.json" or whatever the user names the file


- Export Format
- Exports an array of JSON objects like:

```json
{
  "id": 1732461123456,
  "type": "Screen",
  "label": "Screen",
  "timestamp": 32.841,
  "formattedTime": "0:32",
  "gameClockTime": "9:12 Q1" (if applicable)
}
